29/04/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister Dimitris Droutsas assured visiting Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Ivica Dacic on Thursday (April 28th) of Greece's support for Serbia's EU integration efforts. 
Dacic thanked him and said he expects bilateral relations would be further strengthened. 
While in Athens, Dacic who is also interior minister, met with Greek Citizens Protection Minister Christos Papoutsis to discuss an agreement on mutual recognition of driving licences and a readmission agreement. 
They also discussed co-operation between their respective police services, as well as co-operation in fighting illegal immigration and organised crime. 
(Tanjug, Politika, RTS - 28/04/11)
